TitleFFF 506-2 Feudal Knight MH
Birthday16 Halane 693
AppearanceAge 26, height 5’ 8”, heavy frame, weight 168 lb, attractive appearance, fair complexion, red hair, green eyes
Medical/PsycheNone
Size7
ArmorWhen not expecting combat: Cloth dress, vest and cap; leather shoes; dagger and broad-sword. In combat: Quilt cowl, gambeson and leggings; leather knee boots and gauntlets; mail cowl, hauberk, leggings and mittens; plate ¾ helm, kneecops, and coudes; and a kite shield. A plate breastplate is added for tournaments
Other EquipmentBelt pouch
Valuables£1 in gold, 71d in silver in a money pouch
NotesUnless she has no other choice, Dame Afaewynn primarily fights from horseback. Her encumbrance is halved while mounted.

Biography

Dame Barthy is the 26-year-old only child of Sir Edwin Barthy, Bailiff of Ovendel manor, Thelshire. Afaewynn’s mother died in childbirth. Her father never remarried and raised her as somewhat of a tomboy – teaching her to ride and fight. At age 17, her father arranged a marriage to a knight in the Earl of Balim’s household guard stationed at Kiban – a year later, he was killed in a riding accident while hunting. Afaewynn claimed her husband’s horse, armour and weapons, and returned to Ovendel. After proving herself in combat against a group of brigands, she was knighted by a friend of the family and started fulfilling Ovendel’s feudal levy in place of her aging father. An attractive woman, excellent rider and a competent warrior, she has considerable skill with a lance. Despite this, or because of it, few male knights will give her the time of day. She has little chance of marrying again.

She attends tournaments out of a need to prove to the male knights that she is just as good as they are – if not better. Dame Barthy has an extreme dislike for Sir Kathel Dezaller of Loban, one of her goals is to beat him at the joust. If she is not confirmed as the bailiff of Ovendel, on the passing of her father, Dame Barthy will be without a means of support. She has set aside tournament winnings and made investments with the usurers in Tashal as an insurance policy. Afaewynn has developed a friendship with Dame Trina of Kallin, a Lady of Paladins Knight from Whyce manor. Dame Trina has encouraged Afaewynn to join the fighting order.

Adventure Hooks

Tournament Time: PC knights may face Dame Barthy on the list field. A loss to her could be embarrassing for their reputation.

Nefarious Scheme: The PCs have been hired to take some action against a noble woman. Dame Barthy is serving as the woman’s bodyguard.

Rumours: Someone is spreading rumours calling Dame Afaewynn’s character into question. She hires the PCs to investigate and find out who is spreading the lies.

Bailiff of the Manor: Dame Barthy has been confirmed as the new Bailiff of a manor house. PCs are from the manor and must work with their new Lady.

An Encounter on the Road: During the tournament season, Dame Barthy travels extensively and can be encountered on the roads of Kaldor as a fellow traveller, or in some other capacity.

Rescuer/Rescuee: An ambush by bandits has put the PCs in need of rescue, or conversely put Dame Barthy in need of rescue by the PCs.
